<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Kim Jong-un inspects nuclear-capable aircraft on Russian visit]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/kim-jong-un-inspects-nuclear-capable-aircraft-russia-visit]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T13:19:43Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b0899302716d92b1a1e31d46d2bf1e020549c6eb/0_51_910_546 /master/910.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=42cfab4fc5620c5f88bebc1e300acf70&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;金正恩身着西装，两侧是谢尔盖·绍伊古和另一名俄罗斯军官，两人都穿着制服，走过机场，一群人跟着他们&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;朝鲜领导人金正恩在弗拉基米尔·普京国防部长的陪同下视察了俄罗斯的核战略轰炸机、高超音速导弹和军舰。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;周六，谢尔盖·绍伊古在距离太平洋港口城市符拉迪沃斯托克约 30 英里（50 公里）的俄罗斯内维奇机场迎接金正恩。朝鲜领导人随后检阅了仪仗队。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国和韩国担心，莫斯科与平壤友谊的恢复可能会让金正恩获得俄罗斯的一些敏感导弹技术，同时帮助武装俄罗斯参加朝鲜战争。乌克兰。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯国防部表示，绍伊古展示了 Kim 战略轰炸机——Tu-160、Tu-95 和 Tu-22M3——它们能够携带核武器，构成俄罗斯核空中攻击力量的骨干力量。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“它可以从莫斯科飞往日本，然后再飞回来，”绍伊古向金介绍一架飞机。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;金有时会询问飞机是如何发射导弹的点头微笑。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/15/vladimir-putin- kim-jong-un-summit- Russia-north-korea-meeting- Five-things&quot;>;弗拉基米尔·普京与金正恩峰会：我们学到的五件事&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;绍伊古向他展示了配备“匕首”空​​射高超音速导弹的 MiG-31I 超音速拦截机，该导弹能够携带核弹头或常规弹头。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据报道，该导弹的射程为 1,500-2,000 公里（930- 1,240 英里），同时承载高达 480 公斤（1,060 磅）的有效负载。它的飞行速度可达音速的 10 倍。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯驻朝鲜大使亚历山大·马采戈拉 (Alexander Matsegora) 告诉记者，金正恩的行程“非常紧张”，目前尚不清楚他将在朝鲜停留多久据俄罗斯国家通讯社俄新社报道，俄罗斯。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄新社称，金正恩在符拉迪沃斯托克视察了俄罗斯太平洋舰队的沙波什尼科夫元帅号护卫舰，并观看了现代导弹控制系统的演示。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;韩国美国周五表示，朝鲜和俄罗斯之间的军事合作将违反联合国对平壤的制裁，盟友将确保付出代价。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯不遗余力地宣传金正恩的行为访问并多次暗示与朝鲜进行军事合作的前景，朝鲜是在苏联的支持下于 1948 年建立的。对于弗拉基米尔·普京来说，他表示莫斯科陷入了与朝鲜的生存之战。向西越过乌克兰，向金正恩示好可以让他刺痛华盛顿及其亚洲盟友，同时有可能为乌克兰战争确保大量火炮供应。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;华盛顿指责朝鲜向俄罗斯提供武器，而俄罗斯拥有世界上最大的武器装备。数量最多的核弹头，但尚不清楚是否已交付任何核弹头。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周五，金正恩视察了一家受到西方制裁的俄罗斯战斗机工厂。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他和俄罗斯总统周三会晤时讨论了军事问题、乌克兰战争和深化合作。普京告诉记者，俄罗斯“不会违反任何规定”，但会继续发展与朝鲜的关系。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;克里姆林宫发言人德米特里·佩斯科夫 (Dmitry Peskov) 告诉记者，目前还没有签署任何正式协议的计划访问期间。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯外交官表示，在美国支持其世界各地的盟友之后，包括美国一艘核弹道导弹潜艇7月份访问韩国，华盛顿无权对莫斯科说教。据俄新社报道，金正恩在符拉迪沃斯托克观看了圣彼得堡马林斯基剧院上演的芭蕾舞剧《睡美人》的第一幕。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 21:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘You can’t unsee it’: the mental toll of Maui fires on search-and-rescue teams]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/16/maui-wildfires-search-and-rescue-workers-mental-health]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T11:00:30Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/5724c77a9856cd0b7715e999ffb9dbe2b097d181/0_285_5899_3540 /master/5899.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1535e48c1e306a11afc2f90798a2a9c7&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;两名搜救人员和一条狗在废墟中&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;在拉海纳日的废墟中漫步日复一日，在被毁坏的房屋废墟和灰烬覆盖的街道之间，埃里克·达林会努力记住他的座右铭。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“每个人都回家了，”这位退休的加州消防员会告诉自己。 “包括我。”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/14/us-forest -service-wildfire-fighters-low-pay&quot;>;压力和薪酬驱动美国野火战士出走：“疲劳是真实的”&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;训犬师已前往岛上和他的狗 Mazie 一起，作为联邦紧急事务管理局团队的一员，协助开展严峻但至关重要的人类遗骸打捞工作。任务是搜查每一个建筑物以找到死者，为悲痛的家庭提供一个结局，并为社区提供答案。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这样的部署对于达林和其他像他一样在现场和在现场的人来说意味着额外的责任未来几年：应对目睹大规模死亡和破坏所造成的精神创伤。随着致命灾难的频率和规模不断增加，对搜索和恢复团队的要求也越来越迫切。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在前往毛伊岛之前，达林曾对&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com /environment/2018/dec/20/last-day-in-paradise-california-deadliest-fire-untold-story-survivors&quot;>;2018 年营地火灾&lt;/a>;，摧毁了天堂镇，造成 85 人死亡。两年后，他成为&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/dec/30/california-wildfires-north-complex-record”后搜寻遗骸的团队成员之一&quot;>;North Complex 火灾&lt;/a>;导致 16 人死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“那些大火灾，它们会陪伴你一段时间，”达林说。 “在毛伊岛再次看到它，有很多似曾相识的感觉。纯粹的破坏对我打击很大。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;夏威夷王国历史首都拉海纳的破坏震惊了居民和经验丰富的应急人员。大火蔓延得如此之快和猛烈，以至于没有收到官方警告的居民&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/15/lahaina-survivor-hawaii-fires&quot; >;努力撤离&lt;/a>;。大火烧毁了海滨社区，至少 97 人死亡。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/2023/09/15/coming-up-mpd-discuss-latest-number-unaccounted-following-lahaina-fire/&quot;>;三十一个&lt;/a>;人员仍然失踪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;•&lt;/span>;&lt;span>;•&lt;/span>;&lt;span>;•&lt;/span>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;应急人员的工作就是揭示了致命灾难的真实死亡人数。在重大野火后寻找死者是一项艰巨的任务，需要数百名搜救人员，从法医人类学家到训练有素的犬只训练人员，以探测人类遗骸。这些团队仔细搜寻废墟，在拉海纳，一些团队已经出海寻找可能的受害者。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对于像达林和希瑟·弗格森这样的训犬师来说，他们带着来自俄亥俄州的工作组，每天从凌晨 4 点左右开始。他们带着黑色拉布拉多犬 Mazie 和比利时玛利诺犬 Melvin，在日出后开始搜索，从早上 6 点工作到下午 6 点。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在毛伊岛，这些狗在一片茂密的土地上穿行，而同时他们的管理人员密切关注危险，例如岛上的野鸡在燃烧区域漫步，并试图确定一个财产的结束位置和其他财产的开始位置。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“它实际上是一个又一个结构。我们将这些狗放入剩下的任何地方，让它们在该结构中工作，然后将它们转移到下一个结构中。”弗格森说。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/19/canada-wildfires-firefighters-shortage&quot;>;“打一场必败仗”：一波又一波的野火让加拿大志愿消防员精疲力尽&lt;/a>;&lt; /p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;如果狗发出警报（通常是通过吠叫），法医人类学家将确定是否存在人类遗骸。被部署到毛伊岛的加州州立大学奇科分校的法医人类学家科琳·米利根 (Colleen Milligan) 说，建筑材料和干墙有时可能类似于人骨。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;米利根在这一领域拥有丰富的经验，她和她的科罗拉多州立大学奇科分校在这方面拥有丰富的经验。团队帮助 85 名受害者中的 75 名康复&lt;/a>;篝火烧毁了邻近的一个城镇。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“让我们震惊的不是有什么不同，而是有多少相同，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一旦人类遗骸被运出，确定后，团队仔细检查该区域，通常是用抹子和刷子用手和膝盖进行修复，以尽可能地恢复。同样在毛伊岛工作的科罗拉多州立大学奇科法医人类学家埃里克·巴特林克 (Eric Bartelink) 表示，他们使用拉力筛选碎片，收集小牙齿、小手骨和小脚骨。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们不想离开火灾受害者身后的任何明显痕迹，”他说。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;fd67ca921d440b0b155292e5b179b2baff2553b9&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/fd67ca921d440b0b155292e5b179b2baff2553b9/0_0_ 3264_2176/ 1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;联邦应急管理局搜救工作队成员正在拉海纳被毁的社区进行搜查。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;667&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;联邦应急管理局搜救工作队的成员在拉海纳被毁的社区中进行搜查。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：FEMA/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/ Figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;这项工作对精神和体力来说都是一种负担。研究小组报告称，在毛伊岛，漫长的白天潮湿又炎热，一些地区的地温高达 160 华氏度（71 摄氏度）。狗穿着靴子来保护它们的爪子，动物和它们的饲养员在一天结束时都接受了净化。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;如此多的破坏的景象是超现实的，但弗格森说她试图把注意力集中在背后的目的上&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我这样做是有原因的，我这样做的原因是因为我可以，”弗格森说。 “归根结底，我知道我可以帮助自己，可以帮助他人，可以为人们带来终结，这就是我这样做的原因。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这项工作的重担可能会持续存在。弗格森是一名独立管理人员，每天担任毒理学家，她说，从部署返回后的头几天，她感到缓慢和迷茫是很常见的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;让队友在现场，帮助她了解情况。弗格森说，在灾难发生期间和灾难发生后，都要把事情讲清楚。弗格森接受的帮助死者康复的训练导致她遇到了一系列紧急情况，从佛罗里达州公寓倒塌到肯塔基州龙卷风和伊恩飓风。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; “归根结底，你无法忽视或体验不到毛伊岛发生的事情，”她说。 “我仍然可以闭上眼睛，想象走过其中一些地方和一些房屋，看到那些可能是我的狗发出警报的东西。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;救灾应急人员返回后需要持续的支持，蒂姆·豪韦林 (Tim Houweling) 说，他是一家非营利组织的联合创始人，帮助急救人员获得替代疗法。他说，问题并不总是立即浮出水面，它们可能会在事件发生后数月甚至数年出现。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/11/everyone-loved-angel-spanish-town-still-griving-for-hero-who-fought-wildfires&quot;>;“每个人都爱天使”：西班牙小镇仍在悲伤对于扑灭野火的英雄&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“面对100%的破坏并不是头脑能够真正理解的事情，”他说。 “我们很多人都会进入任务模式。这是需要处理的事情。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在毛伊岛时，达林很快就抛开了震惊，专注于工作和带人们回家的使命。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但也有一些问题他说，这是你无法准备的事情，就像居民们向他表示的感激之情一样。当他准备登上从毛伊岛起飞的航班时，其他乘客（其中一些是因火灾而流离失所的居民）开始向他鼓掌。他们拒绝在达林和他的狗 Mazie 之前登机。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们的赞扬虽然是善意的，但却令人痛苦。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我没想到会这样。我感觉自己很渺小，”他说。 “我来这里是为了做我的工作。你们失去了家人、生意或住所。我要回家，而你正在另一个州寻求庇护。”&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 19:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Man arrested over trespass at Buckingham Palace stables]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/16/man-arrested-over-trespass-at-buckingham-palace-stables]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T10:28:29Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/a102b57a18fe157af787106cdb9be66c6f52b7fc/0_51_4217_2531 /master/4217.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b0332febc886387c8b9426d8dcff744b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一只狐狸跑过白金汉宫&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;警方收到消息后，一名男子在白金汉宫附近被捕据报道，周六凌晨有人试图爬墙。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;官员称，一名 25 岁的男子因侵入受保护地点而根据《严重有组织犯罪和警察法》被捕。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;大都会警方表示，“白金汉宫的官员对一名爬墙进入皇家马厩的人做出了回应。” “经过搜查，一名 25 岁男子在皇家马厩外被警察拘留。该男子从未进入白金汉宫或宫殿花园。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;皇家马厩位于宫殿花园以南，里面有宫殿马厩和用于仪式场合的金色马车。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;大都会艺术博物馆表示，该男子仍被拘留在伦敦警察局。&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot; _blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 18:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[No cull of American XL bully dogs in UK despite ban – but owners face new rules]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/16/no-cull-american-xl-bully-dogs-uk-despite-ban-new-rules]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T09:34:07Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6af85fd8543863fee732a36f07f13dce8bc93b53/0_1894_5464_3277 /master/5464.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=973f1ba224510868405a56a6e4dc2ff3&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一只美国 XL 恶霸犬&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;英国首席兽医官强调将会有特赦在禁止美国 XL 恶霸犬之前，一位专家表示，自 2021 年以来，几乎一半的针对人类和狗的袭击事件都是由该品种造成的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对 XL 恶霸犬的特赦将意味着现有的动物不会被扑杀， Christine Middlemiss 博士表示，但主人必须进行登记，并在公共场合给它们拴上皮带和口套。周四，西米德兰兹郡的一名男子在被疑似 XL 恶霸犬袭击后死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这是该品种一系列伤人事件中的最新一起 - &lt;a href=&quot;https://www. theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/15/why-are-american-xl-bullies-being-banned-and-how-will-it-work&quot;>;10 起致命的狗袭击事件中的 6 起&lt;/a>;去年在英国发现的 XL 恶霸犬与 XL 恶霸犬有关，而今年的七起恶霸犬中至少有 3 起。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在一些动物慈善机构反对后，劳伦斯·纽波特 (Lawrence Newport) 博士为时代广播电台的禁令提供了理由，他描述了该品种&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“自 2021 年以来，该犬种造成的死亡人数占所有犬只死亡人数的 70% 以上；近 50% 对人类和其他狗的攻击都是由它造成的。今年 7 月的一周内，每天就有一只狗被美国恶霸杀死。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/15/why-are-american-xl-bullies-being-banned-and-how-will-it-work&quot;>;为什么美国 XL 恶霸被禁止它会如何运作？&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;虽然英国皇家防止虐待动物协会 (RSPCA) 和其他机构认为，将该品种添加到英国禁止饲养的狗的名单中会为了阻止袭击事件的增加，纽波特将斗牛犬的袭击进行了比较，自 1991 年《危险犬类法案》以来一直立法禁止斗牛犬袭击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这项禁令非常成功。我们知道这一点，因为例如，在英国，我们的人均狗死亡人数是美国的一半，而这种差异完全是由斗牛犬造成的，”他说，并补充说，该品种造成了约 60% 的死亡。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Middlemiss 告诉 BBC Radio 4 的 Today 节目，禁止 XL 恶霸犬只是其中一项措施，并强调了解这些动物在该国的位置的重要性。 “还有大量工作正在进行，涉及负责任的饲养、负责任的饲养以及对饲养可能具有危险性的狗的人进行教育。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但围绕该禁令实施的时间表仍存在疑问。 。食品和农业部长马克·斯宾塞议员周五警告说，禁止该品种得到了皇家养犬俱乐部的正式认可，“并不像看起来那么简单”，而且可能需要比预期更长的时间。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;“我们必须经历识别该类型狗的特征的过程，并确保我们不会在此过程中封装错误类型的狗。这需要一些时间才能做到这一点，”他告诉 BBC 的《有什么问题吗？》计划。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;品种，是&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/sep/15/why-are-american-xl-bullies-being -banned-and-how-will-it-work&quot;>;2014 年左右首次引入英国&lt;/a>;，近年来人气飙升，但缺乏有关其数量的可靠数据。尽管该品种造成了很高比例的致命袭击，但推动禁令的 Bully Watch 组织认为，它们只占全国所有养狗的不到 1%。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 17:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Newborn baby found dead on boat crossing Mediterranean to Italy]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/newborn-baby-boat-rescue-operation-lampedusa-italy]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T08:59:07Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/3c2297ec806c7e226d0f14985edfeee9e4ea857c/0_45_3926_2355 /master/3926.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=8eaea1e332b06b21fc1910d2b83fa154&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;裹着金色应急毯的人们站在石岛上的海岸警卫队船上&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;据安莎通讯社报道，在一次救援行动中，一艘载人前往意大利兰佩杜萨岛的船上发现一名新生婴儿死亡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这名婴儿在旅途中出生，出生后不久就去世了，据安莎社报道，并补充说船上约有 40 人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;本周早些时候，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/13/ Five-month- old-baby-boy-drows-in-rescue-mission-off-lampedusa&quot;>;在兰佩杜萨岛附近的一次救援行动中，一艘载人从北非穿越大海的船只翻覆，导致五个月大的男孩溺水身亡。&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;今年已有近 126,000 名移民抵达意大利，几乎是 2022 年同期数字的两倍。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href= “https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/13/ Five-month-old-baby-boy-drowns-in-rescue-mission-off-lampedusa&quot;>;五个月大的男孩溺水身亡兰佩杜萨岛附近的救援任务 &lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;根据救援机构的数据，本周周一至周三，约 8,500 人（超过兰佩杜萨岛的全部常住人口）乘坐 199 艘船抵达该岛。联合国移民机构。难民涌入促使当地政界人士呼吁帮助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;意大利总理乔治亚·梅洛尼 (Giorgia Meloni) 周五呼吁欧盟“在必要时与海军特派团”联合采取行动，防止人们穿越地中海北非。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在社交媒体上发布的视频消息中，梅洛尼承诺采取严格行动，应对本周入境人数的增加。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“意大利自疫情爆发以来一直面临移民压力。 “今年年初的经济增长是不可持续的，”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她说，这个问题源于非洲“困难的国际局势”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她敦促欧盟委员会主席乌苏拉·冯 (Ursula von)德莱恩访问兰佩杜萨，并要求欧洲理事会主席查尔斯·米歇尔将此事列入理事会10月峰会议程。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 17:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘We need to start again’: Morocco’s earthquake puts girls’ education at risk]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/we-need-to-start-again-moroccos-earthquake-puts-girls-education-at-risk]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T08:00:24Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/15da841a4b72dffee47c712a3b57a8759b33fabb/0_0_8640_5760 /master/8640.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=018e930b10e2b35503662c02cd14414a&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 的一座建筑物部分倒塌后倾斜&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;发生强烈地震时上周五晚上，在摩洛哥阿特拉斯山脉深处，新学年才刚刚开始。一家女童教育慈善机构工作到很晚的工作人员突然发现自己受到了 6.8 级地震的冲击，办公室的墙壁倒塌，暴露在寒冷的山间空气中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“许多人我们认识的至少还活着的女孩中，有一半失去了母亲、兄弟、父亲和家人，而且看起来她们的许多房屋也被完全摧毁了，”&lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /www.globalgiving.org/projects/earthquake-crisis-appeal/&quot;>;全民教育&lt;/a>;，她的声音沙哑。该慈善机构支持阿特拉斯山脉上由六所女孩寄宿所组成的网络，这些寄宿所均位于地震震中周围的村庄。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;瞬间，地震的力量将寄宿所的墙壁撕裂，基础设施薄弱的山区需要这些资源，否则那里的学校可能很难进入 - 并且&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.efamorocco.org/about-us/&quot;>;17年的工作&lt;/a>;确保阿特拉斯地区的女孩能够接受教育。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在偏远村庄 Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 的一所容纳 52 名学生的寄宿处，一名主管拍摄了她卧室的废墟。 “看看地震期间落在我身上的所有这些碎片，”她说，她的淡紫色床架上堆放着裸露的砖块，周围是成堆的碎玻璃和建筑物外部的碎片。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/12/ordinary-moroccans-bring-aid-to-quake-hit-villages -amid-criticism-of-of-ficial-response&quot;>;在官方反应受到批评的情况下，普通摩洛哥人向受地震袭击的村庄提供援助&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;在最古老的房子里，它位于在阿斯尼村，地震使图书馆的墙壁被撕裂，计算机设备被毁，建筑物无法居住。 “他们在这里度过了整整一周，”其中一间寄宿处的学生协调员 Latifa Aliza 说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;971de1a141386e24cf1dba2e213bc679c1d1ad48&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https:// media.guim.co.uk/971de1a141386e24cf1dba2e213bc679c1d1ad48/0_539_8640_5186/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一台挖掘机正在清理 Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 附近的一条山路。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;一台挖掘机正在清理 Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 附近的一条山路。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Carl Court/Getty Images&lt;/span>; &lt; /figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;“我们需要从头开始，因为这座建筑非常重要，”她补充道，站在被毁坏的宿舍废墟中。该组织表示，六间寄宿处中的五间可能需要拆除并完全重建，其中一些目前甚至无法安全进入。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“现在的情况很困难； “损失太大了，”艾丽莎说。 “我们仍然没有找到所有学生，特别是那些住在 Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 周围地区的学生，该地区仍然很难到达。我们的组织正在尽一切努力来帮助他们。”奥马尔表示，该组织仍在寻找大约三分之一的学生，其中约有 250 名女孩。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;摩洛哥当局估计，地震中有近 3,000 人死亡，超过 5,500 人受伤。地震集中在马拉喀什以南约 43 英里的阿特拉斯山脉深处，但远至摩洛哥北部的卡萨布兰卡和拉巴特等城市，建筑物都发生了震动，人们都惊慌失措地跑上街头。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;震中周围阿尔豪兹地区阿特拉斯山脉上星罗棋布的许多村庄由于其地理位置和救援工作的巨大困难而受到的打击最为严重。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿尔豪兹的大部分地区长期以来都被剥夺了生存权。即使是基本的基础设施，以及许多隐藏在山峰中的最偏远的村庄也只能步行到达。地震发生一周后，余震撼动山峰，村民们骑着驴子或摩托车走过的陡峭山路现在被堵塞或出现危险的裂缝，因为人们担心地震发生一周后余震会震动山峰，导致山体滑坡。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;直升机继续将伤员运送出阿特拉斯山脉寻找剩余幸存者的希望渺茫，并且担心最偏远村民的许多村民在泥砖房屋的废墟下窒息而死，这些房屋倒塌时没有留下任何呼吸的空间。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;摩洛哥国王穆罕默德六世已承诺重建约 50,000 所因地震受损的房屋。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;全民教育的设立是为了确保阿特拉斯地区一些最偏远地区的女孩能够接受教育。对于女孩来说，到达该地区的学校大楼往往面临更大的挑战。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;摩洛哥妇女的受教育率在过去二十年中缓慢上升，但截至 2018 年，64% 的女孩在中学就读，&lt; a href=&quot;https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SE.SEC.NENR.FE?locations=MA&quot;>;根据世界银行&lt;/a>;的数据，摩洛哥只有不到一半的女性记录在案2021 年的&lt;a href=&quot;https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SE.TER.ENRR?locations=MA&quot;>;最新数据&lt;/a>;接受过高等教育。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;奥马尔认为，确保女孩从小就能够进入课堂往往足以彻底改变她们的未来。但由于寄宿处现已成为废墟，她和她的组织正在努力找出阿特拉斯中还剩下哪些教育设施，以及如何让女孩们继续学习，即使这意味着在帐篷里在线学习。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们正在努力查明哪些学校遭到破坏。该地区的许多教师失去了家人和家园。他们睡在外面的临时帐篷里。由于这些村庄非常偏远，这就是我们支持这些社区的原因，因为这意味着滴下来的援助根本无法到达那里。”她说。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id= &quot;5abb16657e726811a1e47b156ecc970c1b9933aa&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/5abb16657e726811a1e47b156ecc970c1b9933aa/0_303_5500_3302/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Chi孩子们在 Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 的帐篷外玩耍&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot; 600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;地震后，Talat N&#39;Yaaqoub 的许多家庭都住在帐篷里。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Ammar Awad/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/图>; &lt;p>;“一些地区电话联系为零，道路被封锁，许多村庄甚至不靠近公路。你必须把车停在一个小时之外然后步行；没有基础设施。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在灾难中，奥马尔发现了一些希望的小迹象。用她的话说，他们的许多前毕业生后来成为“社区的支柱”，现在已经开始协调援助工作。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;阿斯玛·艾特·塔勒布 (Asma Ait Taleb)，一名前学生，后来从地震发生时，马拉喀什大学的她正在回到奥伊俄贞村的家中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“当我在奥伊俄贞这里找到六名前毕业生后，我们就开始尝试寻找其他一些女孩，”她说。 “互联网一恢复，我就开始在任何可能的地方发送消息，在 Instagram 上发布信息，要求女孩们与我们联系并让其他人提供信息。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该组织编制了一份失踪学生名单和开始了他们的搜索，同时走遍了阿特拉斯地区一些最偏远的村庄，分发​​重要的援助物资。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“这次地震也展示了我们地区的优点，”她说。 “我希望事情会比以前更好。我们必须保持希望。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 16:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Sydney marathon runners warned about heat as above average warmth affects south-east Australia]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/16/australia-weather-sydney-marathon-melbourne-heat-warm-temperature-forecast]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T07:35:21Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/546049b235e3d2db84519ebae2b6f3b26a1ff3f7/0_0_6000_4000 /master/6000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9ce6f0e6f44b8d4f674f4fadc13c63c3&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;日落时悉尼天际线上空的烟雾&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;马拉松运动员预计周日会感到闷热，在东海岸一个异常温暖的周末，悉尼气温再次达到 30 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;已有超过 17,000 名跑步者报名参加悉尼马拉松，这是有史以来举办人数最多的马拉松比赛，也是规模最大的马拉松比赛国内的马拉松。但这一事件恰逢高温天气，预计直到周二晚上，悉尼气温将比平均水平高出 10 到 12 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;墨尔本也面临着高于平均水平的高温，预计最高气温将达到 24 摄氏度。星期日。预计气温将高于平均水平 6 到 8 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/ 2023/sep/14/spring-heatwave-for-eastern-australia-a-heads-up-of-whats-to-come-bom-says&quot;>;澳大利亚东部春季热浪“预告”即将发生的事情，气象学家说&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;周六悉尼气温最高达到 30 摄氏度，仅比 9 月份的最高纪录低 4 摄氏度。墨尔本的气温最高为 23 摄氏度，仍比月平均温度高出 6 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;布里斯班的气温达到 26 摄氏度，而阿德莱德则异常温暖，达到 28 摄氏度。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;气象局 ( BoM）预计温暖的天气至少会持续到周中，高级气象学家 Dean Narramore 表示高压系统带来了高温。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“气温将保持在平均水平以上，直到周二左右，届时纳拉莫尔说：“我们将看到一股冷锋穿过，最晚会在周三之前带来一些缓解。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“塔斯曼海有一个非常大且移动非常缓慢的高压系统澳大利亚东南部大部分地区一直吹向北至西北风。”&lt;/p>; &lt;ul>; &lt;li>; &lt;p>;&lt;strong>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/email -newsletters?CMP=copyembed&quot;>;Sign up for Guardian Australia&#39;s free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup&lt;/a>;&lt;/strong>;&lt;/p>;&lt;/li>; &lt;/ul>; &lt;p>;Narramore said the cooler night temperatures meant it was not technically considered a heatwave in Sydney or Melbourne, but added that inland New South Wales, Victoria and South Australia were looking at historically warm September weather.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We could see numerous locations approaching or maybe even exceed their September records, particularly in south-eastern parts around the alpine areas, Wagga Wagga, and well north of Adelaide as well.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While the full Sydney Marathon race was due to commence at 5.45 am, the majority of runners were due to complete the race by 2pm, when the mercury was set to peak for the day.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Organisers said they had been working closely with the Rural Fire Service to review burning activity and expected that forecast winds were set to improve air quality for the event.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The race director, Wayne Larden, said organisers had consulted “extensively” with key stakeholders, including NSW Health, the BoM and the RFS to ensure the safety of runners.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Sydney Marathon is committed to delivering a world-class, safe event for participants on Sunday,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The marathon&#39;s medical director, Hugh Singe, advised participants to ensure they were hydrated, wear appropriate clothing and to seek medical attention when necessary.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“If you feel faint, dizzy, disoriented, or your skin is clammy and abnormally hot or cold, slow down or stop running,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/15 /heat-alert-issued-as-high-temperatures-bring-early-taste-of-summer-to-eastern-australia&quot;>;Heat alert issued as high temperatures bring early taste of summer to eastern Australia&lt;/a>;&lt;/ p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Despite the above-average warmth, Narramore said the weather should not be seen as an early beginning of summer, with temperatures expected to fall later in the week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“With that cold front we&#39;re going to see temperatures return to more typical springtime weather, and could even bring some snow to the mountain areas on Wednesday and Thursday as well,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This is very normal for spring – we have a hot day then a cold day.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It also comes after an AFLW game in western Sydney &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/ sep/16/aflw-game-delayed-by-snake-lying-on-field-in-western-sydney&quot;>;was delayed&lt;/a>; after a snake was spotted sunbathing on the field.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; The red-bellied black snake appeared to be taking advantage of the hot weather, causing a 30-minute delay before a snake handler safely dealt with the intruder.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 15:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia-Ukraine war live: Kim Jong-un meets Russia’s defence minister and inspects nuclear-capable bombers]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/sep/16/russia-ukraine-war-live-kim-jong-un-meets-russias-defence-minister-and-inspects-nuclear-capable-bombers]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T06:06:49Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/b8acb54c36fcdaa810947e65915f99d43a27b124/0_0_5659_3395/master/5659.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=020b56164a8b41d10bcf5945384862b8&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Russian defence minister Sergei Shoigu shows North Korean leader Kim Jong-un Russian warplanes in Vladivostok, Russia, on Saturday&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 14:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[AFLW game delayed by snake lying on field in western Sydney]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/sep/16/aflw-game-delayed-by-snake-lying-on-field-in-western-sydney]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T05:29:10Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/1c6fb1b9f84429b5f8011efbd0e35c212c4a83a2/0_77_2365_1419/master/2365.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=369b8713974d833c16911c3388600d2d&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A snake catcher picks up a snake at the Blacktown International Sportspark&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;An &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/sport/aflw&quot;>;AFLW&lt;/a>; match between Greater Western Sydney and Richmond in Blacktown was delayed after a snake was spotted sunning itself in the grass.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The red-bellied black snake appeared to be taking advantage of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/sep/15/heat-alert-issued-as-high-temperatures-bring-early-taste-of-summer-to-eastern-australia&quot;>;the hot weather that parts of Australia&#39;s south-east&lt;/a>; have been experiencing.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Giants and the Tigers&#39; round three match was pushed back by about 30 minutes while officials waited for a snake handler to arrive at Blacktown International Sportspark.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/aflwomens/status/1702887245902921913&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;Can you believe it! 🐍&lt;br>;&lt;br>; A snake on the field has delayed the clash between the Giants and the Tigers, but we&#39;re almost ready to get underway! &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/FNVx8GXduo&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/FNVx8GXduo&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— AFL Women&#39;s (@aflwomens) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/aflwomens/status/1702887245902921913?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;September 16, 2023&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;When the snake handler did arrive on the scene the snake was identified as a small &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/sep/06/blue-tongue-lizards-are-resistant-to-red-bellied-black-snake-venom-australian-study-finds&quot;>;red-bellied black snake&lt;/a>; – a venomous species found across eastern Australia.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The head of women&#39;s football at GWS, Briana Harvey, said the snake was in one of the far pockets.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“There&#39;s a little red-bellied black snake on the ground at the moment, just in one of the far pockets … obviously for the safety of everyone here we need just to halt the game for the moment,” she told Fox Footy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It is 34 degrees here and we are surrounded by bushland, so I guess it&#39;s not that surprising.”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/sep/14/queensland-man-who-died-after-snake-rescue-on-weekend-did-not-have-venom-in-system&quot;>;Queensland man who died after snake bite incident on weekend did not have venom in system&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The AFLW game started at 1.35pm, after the snake was caught.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Giants were looking for their first win of the season, while the Tigers have won one of their two games so far.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Fans and media were bemused by the very Australian occurrence, and it&#39;s not the only unusual scene involving native wildlife to have unfolded at the venue.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In October last year during a WBBL match Sydney Thunder and Hobart Hurricanes players were sent ducking for cover as the local &lt;a href=&quot;https://au.sports.yahoo.com/cricket-2022-hobart-hurricanes-sydney-thunder-wbbl-bird-attack-021321431.html&quot;>;spur-winged plovers swooped them&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The birds were believed to have laid their nest in the middle of the ground and were fiercely protecting their chicks.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/FoxCricket/status/1582285591575609344&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;These birds woke up on the wrong side of the bed for sure.&lt;br>;&lt;br>; Watch the &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/WBBL08?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#WBBL08&lt;/a>; LIVE on CH503 on &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/Foxtel?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;@Foxtel&lt;/a>; or stream on &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kayosports?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;@kayosports&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/WsEwFL2eob&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/WsEwFL2eob&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Fox Cricket (@FoxCricket) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/FoxCricket/status/1582285591575609344?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;October 18, 2022&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 13:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russell Brand posts video online denying unspecified ‘criminal’ allegations]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/16/russell-brand-posts-video-online-denying-unspecified-criminal-allegations]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T05:23:57Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/cf18a41ebc605e86831fa76e3ffd14788b33ff5e/0_93_3280_1968/master/3280.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=44dd28ac0f0f847aec5f367a930ccc85&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Russell Brand speaks onstage during an event in Los Angeles in 2020.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Actor and comedian Russell Brand has posted a video online saying he “absolutely” denies unspecified criminal allegations about his personal life outlined in two “extremely disturbing letters”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand posted the video on his YouTube and social media accounts on Friday evening, saying he received the letters from a “mainstream media TV company” and a newspaper which he said included a “litany of extremely egregious and aggressive attacks”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He said: “Amidst this litany of astonishing, rather baroque attacks are some very serious allegations that I absolutely refute.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“These allegations pertain to the time when I was working in the mainstream, when I was in the newspapers all the time, when I was in the movies, and as I have written about extensively in my books, I was very, very promiscuous.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand continued: “Now during that time of promiscuity the relationships I had were absolutely, always consensual. I was always transparent about that then, almost too transparent, and I am being transparent about it now as well.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“To see that transparency metastasised into something criminal, that I absolutely deny, makes me question is there another agenda at play.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Brand said he believed he was a part of a “coordinated attack” and that he was going to look into this matter because it was “very, very serious”.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 13:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Second humanitarian crisis’ feared in wake of Libya floods as hopes of finding survivors fade]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/16/second-humanitarian-crisis-feared-in-wake-of-libya-floods-as-hopes-of-finding-survivors-fade]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-16T04:55:08Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/59415d2b60b09b27c42fe7a146afb63a32588aac/0_158_2365_1419/master/2365.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=c158558d739ff99df27e586f8f24f35b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Search teams comb the devastated port city of Derna, Libya, for survivors after flooding estimated to have killed at least 11,000 people&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Aid groups have warned of the growing risk posed by the spread of disease that could compound the humanitarian crisis in Libya, as hopes of finding more survivors fade days after deadly flooding.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Sunday&#39;s flood submerged the port city of Derna, washing thousands of people and homes out to sea after two upstream dams burst under the pressure of torrential rains triggered by the hurricane-strength storm.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Conflicting death tolls have been reported, but official projections of the overall toll have surpassed 11,000.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/15/libya-flood-derna-authorities-seal-port&quot;>;Libyan authorities seal off most of flood-hit Derna in effort to limit deaths&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Aid organisations such as Islamic Relief and Doctors Without Borders (MSF) have warned that the coming period could see the spread of disease as well as grave difficulties in delivering aid to those most in need.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Islamic Relief warned of a “second humanitarian crisis” after the flood, pointing to the “growing risk of water-borne diseases and shortages of food, shelter and medicine”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Thousands of people don&#39;t have anywhere to sleep and don&#39;t have food,” said Salah Aboulgasem, the organisation&#39;s deputy director of partner development.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“In conditions like this, diseases can quickly spread as water systems are contaminated. The city smells like death. Almost everyone has lost someone they know.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;MSF, meanwhile, said it was deploying teams to the east to assess water and sanitation.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“With this type of event we can really worry about water-related disease,” said Manoelle Carton, MSF&#39;s medical coordinator in Derna, who described efforts to coordinate aid as “chaotic”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Libyan authorities have largely sealed off Derna from civilians in an effort to give space to the emergency aid workers and amid concern of contamination of standing water.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Only search and rescue teams would be allowed to enter parts of the town most affected by the flooding, said Salem Al-Ferjani, director general of the ambulance and emergency service in eastern Libya. Many citizens have already left the town voluntarily.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/15/libya-floods-derna-relatives-mourn&quot;>;&#39;The waters carried my son away in front of my eyes&#39;: anguished Libyans mourn lost loved ones&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;But the Red Cross and the World Health Organization (WHO) pointed out that contrary to widespread belief, the bodies of victims of natural disasters rarely pose a health threat. The organisations issued a joint statement on Friday urging Libyans to stop burying the dead in mass graves.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Some may move quickly to bury bodies, such as in mass graves, in part in an attempt to manage this distress, and sometimes because of the fear that these bodies pose a health threat,” the statement said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This approach can be detrimental to the population. Though local authorities and communities can be under immense pressure to bury the dead quickly, the consequences of mismanagement of the dead include long-lasting mental distress for family members as well as social and legal problems”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;An AFP journalist in Derna said central neighbourhoods on either side of the river, which normally dries up at this time of year, looked as if a steam roller had passed through, uprooting trees and buildings and hurling vehicles on to the port&#39;s breakwaters.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Stephanie Williams, a US diplomat and former UN envoy to Libya, urged global mobilisation to coordinate aid efforts in the wake of the flood. She warned of the “predilection of Libya&#39;s predatory ruling class to use the pretext of &#39;sovereignty&#39; and &#39;national ownership&#39; to steer such a process on their own and in a self-interested manner”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In a Friday night news conference, Ahmed al-Mesmari, the spokesperson for east-based military strongman Khalifa Haftar, pointed to “enormous needs for reconstruction”.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/15/what-are-medicanes-the-supercharged-mediterranean-storms-that-could-become-more-frequent&quot;>;What are medicanes? The &#39;supercharged&#39; Mediterranean storms that could become more frequent&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;The UN launched an appeal for more than $71m to assist hundreds of thousands in need and warned the “extent of the problem” remains unclear.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We don&#39;t know the extent of the problem,” UN aid chief Martin Griffiths said on Friday in Geneva as he called for coordination between Libya&#39;s two rival administrations – the UN-backed, internationally recognised government in Tripoli and one based in the disaster-hit east.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Teams from the Libyan Red Crescent are “still searching for possible survivors and clearing bodies from the rubble in the most damaged areas” of Derna, its spokesperson Tawfik Shoukri said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Other teams were trying to deliver much-needed aid to families in the eastern part of the city, which had been spared the worst of the flooding but was cut off by road, he added.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Shoukri pointed to the “very high” level of destruction in the city, but declined to give figures for the number of victims.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While most fear the death toll will be much higher, Tamer Ramadan of the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies said there was still hope of finding survivors, but also declined to give a figure.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The International Organisation for Migration said “over 38,640” people had been left homeless in eastern Libya, 30,000 of them in Derna alone.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Patrick Wintour contributed to this report&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 16 Sep 2023 13:22:01 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>